1 determining whether the alleged unlawful discriminatory practice
2 was based on the religious creed of a person or group, consider
3 whether the alleged unlawful discriminatory practice was
4 motivated by antisemitism.
5 2. As used in this section, “antisemitism” means a perception
6 of Jewish people which may be expressed as hatred toward Jewish
7 people. The term includes, without limitation, rhetorical and
8 physical manifestations of antisemitism directed toward:
9 (a) A Jewish person or non-Jewish person;
10 (b) A Jewish community institution or religious facility; or
11 (c) The property of a Jewish person or non-Jewish person.
